official_title: To require the Secretary of the Treasury to mint coins in commemoration of the 50th anniversary of the United Services Organization.
short_title: United Services Organization's 50th Anniversary Commemorative Coin Act

summary.text: United Services Organization's 50th Anniversary Commemorative Coin Act - Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to mint and issue not more than a specified number of one dollar silver coins to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the United Services Organization (USO). Requires surcharges from the sale of such coins to be deposited in a coinage profit fund and used to fund USO programs and to reduce the national debt. Directs the Secretary to report to the Congress semiannually on activities under this Act.
